The paper deals with a graph matching problem, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The problem involves finding a maximum weighted matching with constraints on the number of edge crossings, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), or cs.CG (computational geometry). The fact that the graph is bipartite and has a 2-layered drawing may also indicate a connection to cs.GT (graph theory) or cs.IT (information theory).
